I view sports betting in a similar way to that of smoking or drinking, but not as harmful. For context, I do not smoke and only drink on occasion.
Where I understand smoking and drinking is harmful to one's health, even in moderation, I do not view moderate gambling as being harmful.
Only when taken to the extreme do I view gambling as harmful.
This is obviously different from one individual to another and their own financial circumstances, and a 50 pounds bet for one person could be much more harmful than a 50 pounds bet to somebody else.
Whereas, if those 2 same individuals smoked 20 cigarettes a day for the rest of their lives, the harm they put themselves at would be similar.
